<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued July 21 at 2:57PM EDT until July 21 at 8:00PM EDT by NWS New York City - Upton</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 315 PM EDT
FOR NORTHERN NEW HAVEN COUNTY...
At 257 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over Plainville, or
near New Britain, moving northeast at 30 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect damage to trees and power lines.
This severe thunderstorm will remain over mainly rural areas of
northern New Haven County.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...&lt;.75 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
